From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Erik Inkinen <erik.inkinen@erikinkinen.fi>
Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 12:15:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] dcomp/tests: add aarch64 stack pointer support

The DirectComposition tests read the current stack pointer to validate call
stack stability around a few entry points. The test already supports x86 and
x86_64 PE builds, but ARM64 PE builds fall into an unconditional
"Unsupported architecture" preprocessor error even though Wine now builds PE
objects for aarch64.

Teach the helper to read the ARM64 stack pointer so the 11.6 test suite
compiles under the Yocto-native clang/lld PE toolchain.
---
 dlls/dcomp/tests/dcomp.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/dcomp/tests/dcomp.c b/dlls/dcomp/tests/dcomp.c
index 96c2eab..59929e7 100644
--- a/dlls/dcomp/tests/dcomp.c
+++ b/dlls/dcomp/tests/dcomp.c
@@ -49,6 +49,12 @@ static void *get_stack_pointer(void)
     __asm__ __volatile__("movq %%rsp, %0"
                          : "=r"(stack_pointer) /* output */
                          :                     /* no input */
+                         :                     /* no clobbered registers */
+    );
+#elif defined(__aarch64__)
+    __asm__ __volatile__("mov %0, sp"
+                         : "=r"(stack_pointer) /* output */
+                         :                     /* no input */
                          :                     /* no clobbered registers */
     );
 #else
-- 
